data.title: Musicians Born on January 25
data.meta_description: Famous birthdays in music for the 25th of January. See which composers, musicians, pop stars and rockers were born on January 25.
data.text:
Johann Gottfried Vierling, German organist and composer, born in Metzels, Duchy of Saxe-Meiningen (d. 1813)

Robert Burns

Scottish poet (Auld Lang Syne) considered the national poet of Scotland, born in Alloway, Scotland

Pablo Hernández Salces, Spanish composer, born in Zaragoza, Spain (d. 1910)

Frederick E. Kitziger, German composer, born in Altenburg, Duchy of Saxe-Altenburg (d. 1903)

Jan Blockx, Belgian opera composer (Sea Bride, Princess of Herberg), born in Antwerp, Belgium (d. 1912)

Giuseppe Radiciotti, Italian musicologist and composer, born in Iesi, Papal States (d. 1931)

Francis George Scott, Scottish composer (Intuitions), born in Hawick, Roxburghshire, Scotland (d. 1958)

Edward Kilenyi, Sr. [Kilényi Ede], Hungarian composer and teacher (Clipped Wings, Outside the Law), born in Békésszentandrás, Hungary (d. 1968)

Wilhelm Furtwängler, German conductor (Berlin Philharmonic, 1922-45, 1952-54), born in Berlin, Germany (d. 1954)

Vladimir Shcherbachov, Soviet-Russian composer (Blokovskaya; The Thunderstorm), and professor (Leningrad Conservatory; Tbilisi Conservatory), born in Warsaw, Poland, Russian Empire (d. 1952)

Florence Mills [Winfrey], American cabaret singer, dancer and comedian, known as 'the Queen of Happiness', born in Washington, D.C. (d. 1927)

"Sleepy" John Estes, American blues musician, born in Ripley, Tennessee (d. 1977)

Julia Smith, American composer (Prairie Kaleidoscope; Cynthia Parker), pianist (Orchestrette Classique), teacher, and musicologist (Aaron Copland: His Work and Contribution to American Music), born in Denton, Texas (d. 1989)

Hendrik Willem Hans Osieck, Dutch pianist and composer, born in Amsterdam. Netherlands (d. 2000)

Witold Lutosławski, Polish pianist, composer, and conductor (Musique funèbre; Trois poèmes d'Henri Michaux), born in Warsaw, Poland (d. 1994)

Ewan MacColl [James Miller], Scottish folk singer-songwriter ("The First Time Ever I Saw Your Face"), born in Broughton, England (d. 1989) [1]

Floyd "Guitar" Smith, American jazz and blues guitarist and record producer, born in St. Louis, Missouri (d. 1982)

Alfred Reed, American composer, born in New York City (d. 2005)

(Farrell) "Rusty" Draper, American country and pop singer ("The Shifting, Whispering Sands"; "Are You Satisfied?"), born in Kirksville, Missouri (d. 2003)

(Wesley) "Speedy" West, American, Country Music Hall of Fame steel guitar player, and record producer, born in Springfield, Missouri (d. 2003)

Giorgos Zampetas, Greek musician and songwriter, born in Athens, Greece (d. 1992)

James Erb, American composer, arranger, and musicologist (Shenendoah), born in La Junta, Colorado (d. 2014)

Antônio Carlos Jobim [Tom Jobim], Brazilian singer-songwriter and composer (Getz/Gilberto), born in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil (d. 1994)

Benny Golson, American jazz tenor saxophonist, arranger, and composer ("I Remember Clifford"), born in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania

Harold Lloyd Jr., American actor (Frankenstein's Daughter), cabaret singer, and son of famous silent film actor Harold Lloyd, Sr, born in Beverly Hills, California (d. 1971)

1931 Stig "Stikkan" Anderson, Swedish music entrepreneur and co-founder of Polar Music (ABBA), born in Hova, Sweden (d. 1997)

Constance Weldon, American symphonic tuba player (Boston Pops; Concertgebouw) and educator, born in Winter Haven, Florida (d. 2020)

1932 Moses "Whispering" Smith, American blues harmonica player and singer ("A Thousand Miles From Nowhere"; "Hound Dog Twist"), born in Union Church, Mississippi (d. 1984)

Etta James

American singer ("Roll With Me"; "At Last"), born in Los Angeles, California

Tami Lynn [Gloria Brown], American soul singer ("I'm Gonna Run Away From You"), and session vocalist (Dr. John; Rolling Stones), born in Gert Town, Louisiana (d. 2020)

Leny Andrade, Brazilian samba, bossa nova and jazz singer, born in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil (d. 2023)

Peter Garland, American composer, and musicologist, born in Portland, Maine

1952 Sara Mandiano [Françoise Castellani], French singer-songwriter, born in France

Malcolm Green, English-born drummer (Split Enz, 1976-81 - "I Got You"), born in United Kingdom

Jan Sandström, Swedish classical music composer (Motorbike Concerto: Snowflakes), born in Vilhelmina, Sweden

Andy Cox, British guitarist (Fine Young Cannibals - "She Drives Me Crazy"), born in Birmingham, England

Edmund Theodore Sylvers, American singer-songwriter and musician (Sylvers), born in Memphis, Tennessee

Gary Brian Tibbs, British rock bassist (Adam & The Ants; Roxy Music), born in London, England

Carl Fysh, British pop-rocker (Brother Beyond - "Can You Keep a Secret?"; "The Harder I Try"), born in Oxford, England

1963 Marcello Giordani, Italian tenor (Metropolitan Opera, 1993-2008), born in Augusta, Sicily (d. 2019)

Heinrich "Haini" Wolfgramm, Polynesian-American actor and musician (The Jets), born in San Francisco, California

Jesse Harte, American heavy metal vocalist (Southgang-Tainted Angel), born in Rome, Georgia

1969 Kina Cosper, American rock and R&B singer (Brownstown), born in Detroit, Michigan

Ana Ortiz, American actress (Ugly Betty - "Hilda"), and singer, born in Manhattan, New York

Jonathan Bryan Colling, American pop singer (4 Fun - Unbelievable Fun Boys), born in Boston, Massachusetts

Alicia Keys

American pop and R&B singer-songwriter, and pianist ("Girl On Fire"; 'No One"), born in New York City

1981 Toše Proeski, Macedonian pop-rock singer, born in Prilep, Macedonia (d. 2007)

Sho Sakurai, Japanese J-pop and hip-hop singer-songwriter, and actor, born in Tokyo, Japan

Andrée Watters, Canadian pop-country-rock singer, born in Quebec City, Quebec

Tina Karol [Tetyana Hryhorivna Liberman], Ukrainian pop singer, born in Orotukan, Russia

Sheryfa Luna, French R&B singer, born in Évreux, France

Ariana DeBose, American actress and singer (West Side Story), born in North Carolina

Lil Mosey

American rapper (Blueberry Faygo), born in Mountlake Terrace, Washington
